keep-with-next.within-column="always" hyphenate="false">Part I. The People of the World</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block text-align="center" font-size="20.736pt" space-before="15.552pt" font-weight="bold" font-style="italic" font-family="Arial, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, sans-serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats">אומות העולם - Umot haOlam</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block>
        <fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em"><fo:inline font-style="italic"> Umot haOlam</fo:inline> is translated as "The People of the World".</fo:block>
        <fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em">Every human being takes an oath in utero to be righteous(Niddah 30b, Iyov). The
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">Umot haOlam</fo:inline> have forsaken this oath.</fo:block>
        <fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em">Every human being has 248 bones that desire to do <fo:inline font-style="italic">mitzvot</fo:inline>(Rambam
            from Sefer Mitzvot). The <fo:inline font-style="italic">Umot haOlam</fo:inline> forsake this desire.</fo:block>
        <fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em">Every human being who's spirit moves them, can obtain understanding and with his
            knowledge set himself different and stand before <fo:inline font-style="italic">haShem</fo:inline>, to serve
            and minister to Him and to know <fo:inline font-style="italic">haShem</fo:inline>, walking straight as
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">Elokim</fo:inline> made him, and and can remove the yoke of the thoughts of
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">bnei Adam</fo:inline>. This human being is sanctified like the
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">Kadosh Kadoshim</fo:inline>. <fo:inline font-style="italic">haShem</fo:inline> is his portion and
            heritage forever and will provide what is sufficient for him in this world like He
            provides for priests and Levites. Thus David, peace be upon him, said<fo:footnote><fo:inline><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">2</fo:inline></fo:inline><fo:footnote-body font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="8pt" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" text-align="justify" start-indent="0pt" end-indent="0pt" text-indent="0pt" hyphenate="true" wrap-option="wrap" linefeed-treatment="treat-as-space">
                <fo:block><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">2</fo:inline>Tehillim 16:5</fo:block>
            </fo:footnote-body></fo:footnote> "haShem is my lot and my portion; You are my cup; you support my lot." <fo:footnote><fo:inline><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">3</fo:inline></fo:inline><fo:footnote-body font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="8pt" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" text-align="justify" start-indent="0pt" end-indent="0pt" text-indent="0pt" hyphenate="true" wrap-option="wrap" linefeed-treatment="treat-as-space">
                <fo:block><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">3</fo:inline>Rambam, Mishneh Torah, Hilchot Shemita v'Yovel 13:13</fo:block>
            </fo:footnote-body></fo:footnote></fo:block>
        <fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em">Every living thing with blood in its body has an animal soul called a <fo:inline font-style="italic">nefesh
                behemut</fo:inline>. All <fo:inline font-style="italic">nefeshot behemut</fo:inline> emanate from some type
            of <fo:inline font-style="italic">klipah</fo:inline> depending on what type of <fo:inline font-style="italic">nefesh
                behemut</fo:inline> it has. <fo:inline font-style="italic">Umot haOlam</fo:inline> have animal souls that
            emanate from three <fo:inline font-style="italic">klipot</fo:inline> that are impure called <fo:inline font-style="italic">klipat
                tameyut</fo:inline>.</fo:block>
        <fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em">Also, all human beings have a Godly soul called a <fo:inline font-style="italic">nefesh Elokit</fo:inline>.
            The <fo:inline font-style="italic">nefesh Elokit</fo:inline> is revealed in the <fo:inline text-decoration="underline">Umot haOlam</fo:inline>. It hovers over them and is distant from them as what is
            called <fo:inline font-style="italic">makif rachok</fo:inline>.<fo:footnote><fo:inline><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">4</fo:inline></fo:inline><fo:footnote-body font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="8pt" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" text-align="justify" start-indent="0pt" end-indent="0pt" text-indent="0pt" hyphenate="true" wrap-option="wrap" linefeed-treatment="treat-as-space"><fo:block><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">4</fo:inline>Ginsburgh, Kabballah and Meditation for the Nations, page 55-56</fo:block></fo:footnote-body></fo:footnote></fo:block>
